Comment: 10,0:00:07.00,0:00:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't something interesting happen for once?
Comment: 10,0:00:09.74,0:00:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just bored to death every single day.
Comment: 10,0:00:12.14,0:00:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all rules, work, and punishment.
Comment: 0,0:00:14.68,0:00:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Chán.
Comment: 10,0:00:15.52,0:00:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting outta this stuffy school for good.
Comment: 10,0:00:18.74,0:00:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When's that?
Comment: 10,0:00:19.87,0:00:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow.
Comment: 10,0:00:21.10,0:00:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You said the same thing just the other day.
Comment: 10,0:00:23.50,0:00:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it this time!
Comment: 0,0:00:25.85,0:00:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Hử?
Comment: 10,0:00:27.02,0:00:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what's got you so focused?
Comment: 10,0:00:29.74,0:00:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing research about the Words.{## we're sticking with this? fine by me; also what do you prefer research on or research about?}{on usually}
Comment: 10,0:00:31.87,0:00:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Words, huh? \NThat's all you've been about these days.
Comment: 10,0:00:35.39,0:00:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If I keep looking for the Words,\NI'm sure I'll find Chariot!
Comment: 10,0:00:38.39,0:00:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the Shiny Rod that will lead me to the Words!
Comment: 0,0:00:42.71,0:00:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Hả?
Comment: 0,0:00:45.61,0:00:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1}LUNA NOVA\NMÔN LỊCH SỬ
Comment: 10,0:00:48.78,0:00:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Ursula!
Comment: 10,0:00:50.82,0:00:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, the Shiny Rod!
Comment: 10,0:00:55.12,0:00:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The fifth Word, I see.
Comment: 10,0:00:57.30,0:01:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is related to ancient history and tradition.
Comment: 10,0:01:00.24,0:01:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,History and tradition?
Comment: 10,0:01:02.87,0:01:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's—
Comment: 10,0:01:05.79,0:01:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When can I expect the materials\NI requested you to collect?{## "request of you" implies the materials are ursula's to begin with, and i think she was just tasked to pick them up from the library shelves/archives}
Comment: 10,0:01:08.94,0:01:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,M-My apologies!
Comment: 10,0:01:10.25,0:01:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right there!
Comment: 10,0:01:11.63,0:01:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, and right when the Cavendish family is having a crisis...
Comment: 10,0:01:16.80,0:01:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Akko! Just give me a minute.
Comment: 10,0:01:21.07,0:01:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Heave-ho! {I always hate these "make an old man sound" lines}{## yeah. shikata ga nai}
Comment: 10,0:01:25.08,0:01:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The Cavendish family? \NI wonder if something happened to Diana.
Comment: 10,0:01:29.75,0:01:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget Diana!
Comment: 10,0:01:32.05,0:01:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at the club the other night, and I heard that the legendary Holy Grail is in Brightonbury. {##}
Comment: 10,0:01:38.03,0:01:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The legendary Holy Grail?
Comment: 10,0:01:40.12,0:01:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumor says the Grail's been carefully tucked away over in Appleton Academy.
Comment: 10,0:01:46.08,0:01:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems that it was used in one of Appleton's\N{\fax-0.2}traditional{\i0} ceremonies of some sort.
Comment: 10,0:01:50.51,0:01:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And Appleton Academy was...
Comment: 10,0:01:52.42,0:01:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a famous school with over\None thousand years of history to its name.
Comment: 10,0:01:56.04,0:01:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Croix!
Comment: 10,0:01:57.31,0:02:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I didn't intend to eavesdrop.
Comment: 10,0:02:01.37,0:02:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, I was surprised to learn that you're looking for the Words.
Comment: 10,0:02:05.01,0:02:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know about the Words?
Comment: 10,0:02:07.87,0:02:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you have some idea of the one that's related to history and tradition?
Comment: 10,0:02:12.73,0:02:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to disappoint, but researchers of modern magic tend not to be well read in ancient magic.
